How to add the code to git and Github.

Before adding files to git repository, ignore some of the files like ".pytest_cache, reports":
    - touch .gitignore                                              (create a folder)
    - ls                                                            (get a list of files)
    - ls -la                                                        (get a list of files)
    - vi .ignore                                                    (to start entering files to ignore)
    - .idea/  and  .pytest_cache/  and  *.log  and  *__pycache__    (Enter some of the folders to ignore)
    - press "escape" and ":wq"                                      (to save folders)

1. Initialize git repository:
    - git init
1.1 To reset files added to git repository:
    - git reset
2. To get git status:
    - git status
3. To add files to staging area:
    - git add .    or    - git add *    or    - git add -A
4. To configure git, run only one time:
    - git config --global user.name "topppi"
    - git config --global user.email "dmitriyqw1@gmail.com"
    To check that configuration is successful:
    - git config --global --list
5. To commit files run:
    - git commit -m "first commit"
6. To push/add files to Github from Master branch run::
    - git remote add origin https://github.com/ToPPPi/Framework_1.git
    - git branch -M main
    - git push -u origin main